\c 9
\p
\v 1
\d To the director, according to Muth-Labben,\f + Uncertain meaning.\f* a psalm of David
\q1
\v 2 I will praise YHWH with all my heart,
\q1 I will recount all your marvellous deeds.\f + Niphal Participle Fem Pl.\f*
\q1
\v 3 I will be glad and rejoice in you,
\q1 I will praise your name O Most High.
\q1
\v 4 When my enemies turn back,
\q1 They stumble and perish before you.
\q1
\v 5 For you have done my justice and my claim,
\q1 You dwell on the throne judging righteousness.\f + Ps 24:9?\f*
\q1
\v 6 You rebuke the nations, you destroy the wicked,\f + Cf. Ps 15:4?\f*
\q1 Their name you wipe out forever.
\q1
\v 7 The enemy is finished in everlasting waste
\q1 And cities you tear up
\q1 Memory of them has perished.
\q1
\v 8 But YHWH sits forever,
\q1 Standing firm to judge on his throne.
\q1
\v 9 And he will judge the world in righteousness,
\q1 He will judge the peoples in uprightness.
\q1
\v 10 And YHWH is a stronghold for the oppressed,
\q1 A stronghold for times in distress.
\q1
\v 11 Those who know your name trust in you,
\q1 For you do not abandon those who seek you, O YHWH.
\q1
\v 12 They praise YHWH who sits on Zion,
\q1 They tell his deeds among the peoples.
\q1
\v 13 For he who demands (avenges) blood remembers them,
\q1 He does not forget the cry of the afflicted.\f + Ps 15:5.\f*
\q1
\v 14 Be gracious to me, O YHWH!
\q1 See my affliction from those who hate me,
\q1 The one who lifts me from the gates of death.
\q1
\v 15 In order to recount all your praises at the gates of the daughter of Zion,
\q1 I will shout for joy in your salvation.\f + Ps 24:5.\f*
\q1
\v 16 The nations sink in the trap they made,
\q1 In this net they set up secretly their feet are caught.
\q1
\v 17 YHWH is known, he does justice,
\q1 In the work of his hand the wicked are ensared.\qs Higgaion. Selah\qs*
\q1
\v 18 The wicked return to Sheol,
\q1 All nations who forget God.
\q1
\v 19 For he will not forget the poor forever,
\q1 Nor will the hope of the afflicted perish forever.
\q1
\v 20 Arise, O YHWH, do not let man defy,
\q1 Let the nations be judged before you.
\q1
\v 21 Put them in fear\f + NRSV/ESV; word uncertain to me.\f*, O YHWH,
\q1 Let the nations know they are men.\qs Selah\qs*